<paragraph id="1A1E1A5DFF95FF84B68BFD50A6ADFD67" blockId="3.[174,1233,644,799]" pageId="3" pageNumber="238">
Diagnosis. This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="DDA161DEFF95FF84B4DCFD51A751FD46" baseAuthorityName="Cresson" baseAuthorityYear="1870" box="[692,804,645,670]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Delomerista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="novita">
<emphasis id="28D5C64FFF95FF84B4DCFD51A751FD46" box="[692,804,645,670]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="238">D. novita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but both sexes have distinctly and closely punctate-reticulate metasoma (
